<HL>
   Harsco to Weigh Holders' Plan
</HL>
<DATE>
04/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HSC
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   HARRISBURG -- Harsco Corp.'s president and chief executive
officer, Malcolm W. Gambill, said the company's directors
will consider an investor group's proposal at its next
regularly scheduled board meeting April 24.
   Mr. Gambill said he has sent a letter to the investor
group, the Carlyle Group of Washington, acknowledging receipt
of their letter.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Carlyle's proposal calls for Harsco to sell its troubled
defense group and pay a special $15 cash dividend to
shareholders.
</TEXT>
